### Wedding Gift List API Test File
### This file contains sample HTTP requests for testing all endpoints

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7293
# @baseUrl = http://localhost:5139

### Get all gifts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts
Accept: application/json

### Create a new gift
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Premium Coffee Maker",
  "description": "A high-end automatic coffee maker with built-in grinder and milk frother"
}

### Create another gift
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Kitchen Knife Set",
  "description": "Professional chef knife set with wooden block"
}

### Take a gift (replace {id} with actual gift ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/1/take
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "guestName": "John Smith",
  "version": 1
}

### Release a gift (replace {id} with actual gift ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/1/release
Content-Type: application/json

### Delete a gift (replace {id} with actual gift ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/1
Accept: application/json

### Test error scenarios

### Take a non-existent gift
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/999/take
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "guestName": "Jane Doe"
}

### Take an already taken gift
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/1/take
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "guestName": "Another Guest"
}

### Release a gift that's not taken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/2/release
Content-Type: application/json

### Delete a non-existent gift
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/gifts/999
Accept: application/json